widgets_values:

* Models : https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.2-I2V-A14B-GGUF/tree/main/HighNoise & 
           https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.2-I2V-A14B-GGUF/tree/main/LowNoise ; select any pairs from q3ks to q8_0.
* Vae : https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/blob/main/split_files/vae/wan_2.1_vae.safetensors
* Loras : (1-lightx-high) https://huggingface.co/patientxtr/WAN2.2-14B-Rapid-AllInOne-GGUF/blob/main/wan2.2_i2v_A14b_high_noise_lora_rank64_lightx2v_4step_1022(keysremoved).safetensors

          (3-fastwan) https://huggingface.co/patientxtr/WAN2.2-14B-Rapid-AllInOne-GGUF/blob/main/FastWan_T2V_14B_480p_lora_rank_64_bf16.safetensors

 * alternative ligthx v1030 high : https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/blob/main/LoRAs/Wan22_Lightx2v/Wan_2_2_I2V_A14B_HIGH_lightx2v_4step_lora_v1030_rank_64_bf16.safetensors

nodes.title: NEEDED NODEPACKS
widgets_values:
* CFZ-Caching : installed with comfyui-zluda by default
* GGUF : https://github.com/city96/ComfyUI-GGUF (if you want to use GGUF for clip or models)
* kjnodes : https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-kjnodes
* WanVideoWrapper : https://github.com/kijai/ComfyUI-WanVideoWrapper
* VHS Video Helper Suite : https://github.com/Kosinkadink/ComfyUI-VideoHelperSuite
* ovum-cudnn-wrapper : https://github.com/sfinktah/ovum-cudnn-wrapper (solves vae encoding decoding slowdown with zluda and rocm)

nodes.title: NOTES AND TIPS
widgets_values:
* CFZ CACHING NODES *
- You can basically generate and save any prompt for almost any model (qwen-edit like models which need image input excluded) with "cfz save conditioning" and later use it with "cfz load conditioning" without ever loading the clip model at all.
- The green "prompt" node is "cfz load conditioning" and lets you select and load any prompt you have previously saved, if you save recently and it is not showing just refresh the window it will show up.
- Another node "cfz print marker" allows you to put "markers" in any part of the workflow for example to calculate time between them or just seperate stuff and check it easily when following the log during / later generation. (very useful with "--verbose CRITICAL" startup commandline option for comfy)
 
* if getting OOM in vae , enable "Tiled VAE" node.

* Video length, total steps (both high and low combined) and "half-steps" meaning where to seperate between high and low can be set with the blue nodes.

* Use normal with multiple lora loader selecting multiple loras or seperate lora loaders. The seperate one also uses alternative loras with strength of loras determined by step. You can try and determine if it is any good for you. The "optional lora" is any lora or loras you want to add so connect more or remove it or bypass ifd you don't need that node.

* By default with lightx 1022 loras + fastwan even 3 steps (1+2) is acceptible. Try other values. Without fastwan use 6 steps (3+3)
* finally when you input a resolution it is set for both dimensions of the input image and it is resized to something compatible for wan with the resolution as upper target. 

* If you have sage attention installed as with comfyui-zluda does automatically , choose "sageattn" as attention_mode in model-high and model-low nodes. If you don't have sage or flash etc choose "comfy" in that list.
